tblStrand.Name: ELA-II|A
tblStrand.Description: Types of Writing

tblStrand.Name: ELA-II|A|9-12
tblStrand.Description: The student will write in narrative, expository, descriptive, persuasive and critical modes.

tblStrand.Name: ELA-II|A|9-12|1
tblStrand.Description: Plan, organize and compose narrative, expository, descriptive, persuasive, critical and research writing to address a specific audience and purpose.

tblStrand.Name: MA-II
tblStrand.Description: NUMBER SENSE, COMPUTATION, AND OPERATIONS

tblStrand.Name: MA-II|B
tblStrand.Description: Computation and Operation

tblStrand.Name: MA-II|B|9
tblStrand.Description: Appropriately use calculators and other technologies to solve algebraic, geometric, probabilistic and statistical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-II|B|9|G10
tblStrand.Description: Use proportional reasoning to solve real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-II|B|9|G7
tblStrand.Description: Apply the correct order of operations to simplify and evaluate numeric expressions.

tblStrand.Name: MA-II|B|9|G8
tblStrand.Description: Use rational numbers in complex ways to solve multi-step real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-II|B|9|G9
tblStrand.Description: Use fractions, decimals and percents in multiple representations for estimation and computation to solve real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III
tblStrand.Description: PATTERNS, FUNCTIONS AND ALGEBRA

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|A
tblStrand.Description: Patterns and Functions

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|A|9
tblStrand.Description: Represent and analyze real-world and mathematical problems using numeric, graphic and symbolic methods for a variety of functions.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|A|9|1
tblStrand.Description: Know the numeric, graphic and symbolic properties of linear, step, absolute value and quadratic functions. Graphic properties may include rates of change, intercepts, maxima and minima.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|A|9|4
tblStrand.Description: Apply basic concepts of linear, quadratic and exponential expressions or equations in real-world problems such as loans, investments and the path of a projectile.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|A|9|G6
tblStrand.Description: Generate a table of values from a formula or equation. Graph the result of a formula or linear equation in ordered pair format on a grid.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|A|9|G7
tblStrand.Description: Translate a problem described verbally or by tables, diagrams or graphs, into suitable mathematical language, solve the problem mathematically and interpret the result in the original context.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|B
tblStrand.Description: Algebra (Algebraic Thinking)

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|B|9
tblStrand.Description: Solve simple equations and inequalities numerically, graphically and symbolically. Use recursion to model and solve real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|B|9|1
tblStrand.Description: Translate among equivalent forms of expressions, such as, simplify algebraic expressions involving nested pairs of parentheses and brackets, simplify rational expressions, factor a common term from an expression and apply associative, commutative and distributive laws.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|B|9|10
tblStrand.Description: Create and use recursive formulas to model and solve real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|B|9|12
tblStrand.Description: Understand how slopes can be used to determine whether lines are parallel or perpendicular. Given a line and a point not on the line, find the equations for the lines passing through that point and parallel or perpendicular to the given line.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|B|9|3
tblStrand.Description: Find equations of a line given two points on the line, a point and the slope of the line or the slope and the y-intercept of the line.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|B|9|7
tblStrand.Description: Solve linear equations and inequalities in one variable with numeric, graphic and symbolic methods.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|B|9|8
tblStrand.Description: Find real solutions to quadratic equations in one variable with numeric, graphic and symbolic methods.

tblStrand.Name: MA-III|B|9|G13
tblStrand.Description: Use formulas with more than one variable to solve real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-IV
tblStrand.Description: DATA ANALYSIS, STATISTICS AND PROBABILITY

tblStrand.Name: MA-IV|A
tblStrand.Description: Data and Statistics

tblStrand.Name: MA-IV|A|9
tblStrand.Description: Represent data and use various measures associated with data to draw conclusions and identify trends. Understand the effects of display distortion and measurement error on the interpretation of data.

tblStrand.Name: MA-IV|A|9|G8
tblStrand.Description: Analyze histograms, bar graphs, circle graphs, stem-and-leaf plots and box-and-whisker plots.

tblStrand.Name: MA-IV|A|9|G9
tblStrand.Description: Understand the meaning of and be able to compute minimum, maximum, range, median, mean and mode of a data set.

tblStrand.Name: MA-IV|B|9
tblStrand.Description: Use appropriate counting procedures, calculate probabilities in various ways and apply theoretical probability concepts to solve real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-IV|B|9|2
tblStrand.Description: Use area, trees, unions and intersections to calculate probabilities and relate the results to mutual exclusiveness, independence and conditional probabilities, in real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-IV|B|9|3
tblStrand.Description: Use probability models, including area and binomial models, in real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-V
tblStrand.Description: SPATIAL SENSE, GEOMETRY, AND MEASUREMENT

tblStrand.Name: MA-V|A
tblStrand.Description: Spatial Sense

tblStrand.Name: MA-V|A|9
tblStrand.Description: Use models to represent and understand two- and three-dimensional shapes and how various motions affect them. Recognize the relationship between different representations of the same shape.

tblStrand.Name: MA-V|A|9|1
tblStrand.Description: Use models and visualization to understand and represent various three-dimensional objects and their cross sections from different perspectives.

tblStrand.Name: MA-V|B|9
tblStrand.Description: Apply basic theorems of plane geometry, right triangle trigonometry, coordinate geometry and a variety of visualization tools to solve real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-V|B|9|1
tblStrand.Description: Know and use theorems about triangles and parallel lines in elementary geometry to justify facts about various geometrical figures and solve real-world and mathematical problems.These theorems include criteria for two triangles to be congruent or similar and facts about parallel lines cut by a transversal.

tblStrand.Name: MA-V|B|9|4
tblStrand.Description: Apply the basic concepts of right triangle trigonometry including sine, cosine and tangent to solve real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-V|C|9
tblStrand.Description: Use the interconnectedness of geometry, algebra and measurement to explore real-world and mathematical problems.

tblStrand.Name: MA-V|C|9|G2
tblStrand.Description: Use formulas to solve real world and mathematical problems.
